          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><span class=\"paragraph\">I am still mulling over how to write this chapter. In the meantime, Professor Dan Simon at Cleveland State University has an accessible introduction here:</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\"><a href=\"http://academic.csuohio.edu/simond/courses/eec641/hinfinity.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">http://academic.csuohio.edu/simond/courses/eec641/hinfinity.pdf</a></span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">In one sentence the <marimo-tex class=\"arithmatex\">||(H_\\infty||)</marimo-tex> (H infinity) filter is like a Kalman filter, but it is robust in the face of non-Gaussian, non-predictable inputs.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">My FilterPy library contains an H-Infinity filter. I've pasted some test code below which implements the filter designed by Simon in the article above. Hope it helps.</span></span>"
          }
        }
